Main Objective of JPEG AI
The goal is:
Better Image Quality
        at
Lower Bitrate
using
Artificial Intelligence

JPEG AI targets:
Human visual quality
Very high compression ratios
AI-native multimedia systems

Why JPEG AI Was Developed
Traditional image codecs use:
DCT transforms
Quantization
Entropy coding
Examples:
JPEG
HEVC intra coding
AV1 intra coding

These are mathematically designed systems.
JPEG AI instead uses:
Learned neural networks
Data-driven optimization
End-to-end training

Basic JPEG AI Framework
A simplified framework:
Input Image
      ↓
Neural Encoder
      ↓
Latent Representation
      ↓
Quantization
      ↓
Entropy Coding
      ↓
Bitstream
      ↓
Entropy Decoding
      ↓
Neural Decoder
      ↓
Reconstructed Image

Core Components
1. Neural Encoder

Usually based on:
CNNs
Transformers
Autoencoders

Purpose:
Extract compact latent representation

2. Latent Space Representation
Instead of transform coefficients:
Learned latent features are transmitted

These features represent:
Texture
Edges
Semantics
Perceptual structures

3. Quantization
Latent features are quantized to reduce bitrate.
Research challenge:
Differentiable quantization during training

4. Entropy Coding
Still needed for lossless bitstream compression.

Methods:
Arithmetic coding
Context models
Hyperpriors
Learned entropy models

5. Neural Decoder

Reconstructs image using:
CNN decoder
Transformer decoder
Generative reconstruction

